      "text": [
        " مَكَّةَ ثَلاَثَ مَرَّاتٍ مِنَ اَلدَّهْرِ فَأَذِنَ اَللَّهُ لَهُ فِيهَا سَاعَةً مِنَ اَلنَّهَارِ ثُمَّ جَعَلَهَا حَرَاماً مَا دَامَتِ اَلسَّمَاوَاتُ وَ اَلْأَرْضُ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2315 - Kulayb Al-Asadi narrated from Abu Abdullah (as):\n\"The Messenger of Allah (swt) (peace and blessings be upon him and his family) sought permission from Allah (swt), the Mighty and Majestic, regarding Mecca three times over the course of time. Allah (swt) granted him permission for it during one hour of the day, after which He made it sacred as long as the heavens and the earth remain.\""
        ]
      }
    },
